Sentencas: In this study, we report a novel medium-entropy perovskite oxide of La0.7Sr0.3Co0.25Fe0.25Ni0.25Mn0.25O3-delta (LSCFNM73) with high constitutive entropy (Sconfig) as the cathode material of intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: A medium-entropy perovskite oxide La0.7Sr0.3Co0.25Fe0.25Ni0.25Mn0.25O3-δ as intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells cathode material

Sentencas: The intrinsic properties of phase structure, electrical conductivity, thermal expansion and oxygen adsorption capacity of La1-xSrxCo0.25Fe0.25Ni0.25Mn0.25O3-delta (LSCFNM, x = 0, 0.1, 0.2, 0.3) oxides are evaluated in detail.
Titulo: A medium-entropy perovskite oxide La0.7Sr0.3Co0.25Fe0.25Ni0.25Mn0.25O3-δ as intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells cathode material

Sentencas: The LSCFNM73 oxide exhibits the maximum electrical conductivity of 464 S cm-1 at 800 degrees C and a relatively lower thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) of 15.34 x 10-6 K-1, which is selected as the propriate cathode composition.
Titulo: A medium-entropy perovskite oxide La0.7Sr0.3Co0.25Fe0.25Ni0.25Mn0.25O3-δ as intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells cathode material

Sentencas: The B-site of LSCFNM73 contains four elements which can increase the configuration entropy.
Titulo: A medium-entropy perovskite oxide La0.7Sr0.3Co0.25Fe0.25Ni0.25Mn0.25O3-δ as intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells cathode material

Sentencas: Additionally, NiO-Yttria stabilized zirconia (YSZ) supported fuel cell is fabricated by tape casting, hot pressing-lamination, co-sintering and screen printing technologies.
Titulo: A medium-entropy perovskite oxide La0.7Sr0.3Co0.25Fe0.25Ni0.25Mn0.25O3-δ as intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells cathode material

Sentencas: The fuel cell demonstrates a maximum power density of 1088 mW cm2 at 800 degrees C, and excellent stability at 750 degrees C under 0.75V in 120 h and 10 times thermal cycling between 750 degrees C and 400 degrees C. Therefore, the medium-entropy LSCFNM73 oxide can be applied in IT-SOFCs as a competitive cathode material.
Titulo: A medium-entropy perovskite oxide La0.7Sr0.3Co0.25Fe0.25Ni0.25Mn0.25O3-δ as intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells cathode material
